{
  "texts": [
    "Proof of Lemma A.1.",
    "For part (i), consider the function φ: [0, 1] 2 → [0, 1] 2 that maps an arbitrary position (x L, x R) into the best response positions (x BR L, x BR R), where the right-wing party takes the leftwing's party position as given, and vice-versa.",
    "Similar to the proof of Lemma 1, we have a continuous mapping from a compact, convex set onto itself.",
    "By Brouwer's theorem we are guaranteed a fixed point",
    ", which is the definition of a Nash equilibrium."
  ]
}